"{\"uid\": \"nzherald.co.nz-travel-bizarre-french-laws-that-could-trip-up-paris-olympic-tourists-S25JZYYLPFABDKNQLWD57YDZOE\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"France has particular rules when it comes to pigs, pools and prices that tourists should look out for.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Photo / 123rf  Paris-bound this summer?\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Bywater unearths six bizarre but amusing French laws that could trip up foreign tourists.\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 143, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9919295785470523, \"rank\": 0.008136071299345638, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 150, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Shire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6445352971380222e-29, \"text\": \"Bywater\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Shire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Shire\"}, {\"begin\": 191, \"end\": 197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9301716348022413, \"rank\": 0.07506965361022115, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics swimmers heading to the piscine this summer may need to check their togs or risk being caught out by one of the country's notoriously tight laws.\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pool guidelines for Paris' 11arrondissement stipulate \\\"only tight trunks can be used for swimming\\\".\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 417, \"end\": 422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0563464270323679e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reasoning behind this law, in place since 1903, states that long shorts or boardies and other beachwear risk introducing sand and other contaminants to the pool.\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More recently, 30 French cities outlawed long, concealing bathing robes that covered the face.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 682, \"end\": 688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9301716348022413, \"rank\": 0.07506965361022115, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The law, dubbed the \\\"burkini ban\\\", was upheld by the Conseil d'Etat in 2022, after a protest that it violated civil liberties of the majority Muslim wearers.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conseil_d'\\u00c9tat_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999678198043, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Conseil d'Etat\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conseil_d'\\u00c9tat_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conseil_d'\\u00c9tat_(France)\"}, {\"begin\": 901, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.997388317624247, \"rank\": 0.0026185141353934033, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From this year it will beillegal to smoke on any French beaches.\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9301716348022413, \"rank\": 0.07506965361022115, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So much foregalite.\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These examples of French bureaucracy are \\\"de rigueur\\\" for the country that wrote the rulebook picked up by much of the world.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9301716348022413, \"rank\": 0.07506965361022115, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the introduction of the Code Napoleon 220 years ago, there have been some interesting rules and bylaws that seem purposely designed to bamboozle tourists.\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been claimed you cannot name a pig Napoleon in France.\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1333, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.719341463757484e-48, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}, {\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or such was George Orwell's interpretation of the baffling legal requirements.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Orwell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.216536171026222e-21, \"text\": \"George Orwell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Orwell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Orwell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are five French rules that should be top of mind for anyone visiting France this summer.\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1448, \"end\": 1454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9301716348022413, \"rank\": 0.07506965361022115, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1508, \"end\": 1514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Frenchman found out the hard way in 2008 after he and his pet snail were fined by national rail operator SNCF.\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A ticket conductor decided the passenger's snail was fare-dodging.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rail operator charged \\u20ac7 ($12.60 at the present rate) for a pet ticket at the time.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The passenger was eventually refunded after the resulting media storm, but the rules still stand.\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Animals under 6kg must be transported in a container, and larger pets must be muzzled throughout the journey.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 2006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The cost of a \\\"large\\\" pet fare is set at 50 per cent of a second-class ticket.\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2085, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's one of France's most cliched holiday snaps.It is also illegal after dark.\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not because there are too many of them, but because the picture is patented intellectual property.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the tower's image passed into public domain in 1993, 70 years after the death of architect Gustav Eiffel, the light display was switched on in only 1985.\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2372, \"end\": 2385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gustav Eiffel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Societe d'Exploitation de la Tour Eiffel can stop professional photographers from profiting from the illuminations.\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2466, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Tour_Eiffel_(Hopi_Hari)\", \"score\": 0.9999999995834514, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"la Tour Eiffel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Tour_Eiffel_(Hopi_Hari)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Tour_Eiffel_(Hopi_Hari)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though it is thought to be largely unenforceable, in theory, anyone taking pictures of the 20,000 twinkly lights between nightfall and 1am risks breaking French copyright law.\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2711, \"end\": 2731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copyright_law_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French copyright law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copyright_law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copyright_law_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 or at least it is if you leave the curtains open.\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2785, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You could be fined \\u20ac15,000-30,000 ($27,000-$54,000) if you are found to be visible \\\"au naturel\\\" even in the confines of your hotel room or private residence.\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2944, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite France's reputation for a laissez-faire attitude towards nudity, there are some strict laws around when and where you can be sans clothes.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2954, \"end\": 2960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The law is designed to avoid sexual exhibitionism and prevents people from being visibly naked in public, even if you are on private property.\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Be careful where you choose to get dressed.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite this, nudist beaches maintain popularity with some visitors.\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although, according tothelocal.fr, under French law even visitors to a plage de nudistes can be charged with \\\"disturbing the peace\\\" if someone takes exception to their state of undress.\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3391, \"end\": 3401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999330672790256, \"rank\": 6.693539997845763e-05, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The croissant and \\\"le dejeuner\\\" are sacrosanct.\", \"from\": 3537, \"to\": 3584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are several laws to protect local cafes and employees' rights to enjoy a pause for kai, but also for the establishments serving them.\", \"from\": 3586, \"to\": 3725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Article R4228-19 of the French Labour Code prohibits employees from taking a working lunch at their desks.\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Designed to preserve the hour-long lunch break - a legal right in France - and to bolster custom in the nearby bistros and cafes.\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3900, \"end\": 3906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, there are also strict laws on when and how long particular eateries can open.\", \"from\": 3965, \"to\": 4051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bakeries and boulangeries are demanded to close for 24 hours at least once a week, stock up on baguettes.\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2018, theGuardianreported an award-winning bakery in Lusigny-sur-Barse was fined \\u20ac3000 for working too many hours in a week.\", \"from\": 4158, \"to\": 4285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4214, \"end\": 4231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lusigny-sur-Barse\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lusigny-sur-Barse\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lusigny-sur-Barse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lusigny-sur-Barse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No wonder many will close at 4pm on the dot.\", \"from\": 4287, \"to\": 4331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While there is a lot to commend on protecting workers' hours and keeping the 24-hours culture, arriving after hours at a hotel with nothing to eat is a travel nightmare.\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Plan accordingly.\", \"from\": 4503, \"to\": 4520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French town of Chateauneuf-du-Pape in the Cotes de Rhone is better known for its Grenache wine than its bylaws.\", \"from\": 4522, \"to\": 4637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4526, \"end\": 4537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\", \"score\": 0.999967104937146, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French town\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\"}, {\"begin\": 4541, \"end\": 4560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ch\\u00e2teauneuf-du-Pape_AOC\", \"score\": 0.9915593748968355, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chateauneuf-du-Pape\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ch\\u00e2teauneuf-du-Pape_AOC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ch\\u00e2teauneuf-du-Pape_AOC\"}, {\"begin\": 4577, \"end\": 4582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RMS_Rhone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3292429226188284e-16, \"text\": \"Rhone\", \"types\": [\"Q11446\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RMS_Rhone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RMS_Rhone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, a bizarre bit of legislature ended up on the books in 1954 during the \\\"space craze\\\" that claimed it was illegal to park a flying saucer in the town.\", \"from\": 4639, \"to\": 4796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The law was added as a publicity stunt to market the town to tourists, but the 70-year law has stuck.\", \"from\": 4797, \"to\": 4898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are no records of infringements, but the decree still stands.\", \"from\": 4899, \"to\": 4966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been said you cannot name a pig after the \\\"petit corporal\\\" in France, but this has been dismissed as urban legend.\", \"from\": 4968, \"to\": 5087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5035, \"end\": 5041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It stems from a claim by George Orwell after a translation of his bookAnimal Farmwas rejected.\", \"from\": 5089, \"to\": 5183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5114, \"end\": 5127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Orwell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.216536171026222e-21, \"text\": \"George Orwell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Orwell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Orwell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Publishing laws demanded he rename the villain of the piece from Napoleon to Caesar.\", \"from\": 5184, \"to\": 5268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5249, \"end\": 5257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.719341463757484e-48, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}, {\"begin\": 5261, \"end\": 5267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_Caesar\", \"score\": 0.9998622425293804, \"rank\": 0.00013776382311103108, \"text\": \"Caesar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_Caesar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_Caesar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While much of this is open to interpretation, the republic still has strict laws on naming conventions.\", \"from\": 5269, \"to\": 5372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks to the Code Napoleon, until 1966 there was a list of approved first names that parents had to choose from for their children.\", \"from\": 5374, \"to\": 5506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While this has since been relaxed, all new names must be approved by judges in the \\\"child's best interest\\\" to protect them from ridicule.\", \"from\": 5507, \"to\": 5644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Previous names on the rejected names list include Michael Jackson, Prince William and - yes - Napoleon Bonaparte.\", \"from\": 5646, \"to\": 5759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5696, \"end\": 5711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.24537537461562e-41, \"text\": \"Michael Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 5713, \"end\": 5727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\", \"score\": 0.9869203869699775, \"rank\": 0.013068044678956791, \"text\": \"Prince William\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_IV\"}, {\"begin\": 5740, \"end\": 5748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.719341463757484e-48, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Doing it tough on a luxury 15-day river cruise.\", \"from\": 5761, \"to\": 5808, \"entities\": []}]}"